In the EU, the **legal duty rests with the employer/operator of the plant** — i.e., the company in control of the workplace/process where the explosive atmosphere could occur.

Under the **ATEX Workplace Directive 1999/92/EC**, as implemented in each Member State, the employer must:

- assess explosion risks;
- classify areas where explosive atmospheres may occur into zones;
- prepare/update the **Explosion Protection Document** before the area is put into use;
